Why should you have a Wifi booster? Discover the Best-Selling Model.

published October, 2020, Helen Fisher

Nowadays, the internet is essential for every home. Not only for work, but also for leisure and entertainment. Ultimately, we use it 24/7, so our connection needs to be strong and available at all times.

Is your phone company slowing down your internet?

A major scandal has erupted in the US when it was revealed that a company was fined for intentionally slowing down user's internet to increase additional purchases. Have you ever wondered if your internet was running more slowly than usual? You might be right! Phone companies know how frustrating it is when we can't get the fast connection that we need. Our downloads time out and there's glitches in video calls with our loved ones. Have you ever had a video call completely stop because of a slow connection? It may have been because of your internet provider.

The Importance of Being Connected

A good connection is more necessary than you may think. A proper signal is essential for simply watching a video or playing a videogame without outages. Now that streaming is how we watch videos and movies, wi-fi signals are getting maxed out more than ever. A video call or a download might be lost if you aren’t near the modem.

But, without a doubt, the most important factor is that we also need to be connected outside of the home, especially at work. A bad connection can cause many inconveniences. If you're using a cloud-based system, bad internet speeds could prevent the correct storing of files and documents. Online meetings and online communication systems, like Slack, need a fast and reliable signal to keep your team connected.

Why should you get a signal amplifier?

Whether you use your internet at home or at your place of business, you likely don't have the bandwidth or internet speed that you need. Even in a small apartment, the wi-fi signal may not arrive everywhere. If more than one device is operating with connection to the wi-fi, you can start running into problems that get worse with each user. Use a signal amplifier to boost your wi-fi speed and reliability. 

A wi-fi signal amplifier is a simple and easy solution to internet issues. It connects to your modem and then provides a boost, easing the load on the wi-fi connection. It operates like a mini-modem, so it works anywhere in your home or office. Imagine how much more productive your team will be when they're all up to speed. Picture the peace at home when your family no longer has to fight over whose device gets to be connected to the internet.

However, you need to make sure that you're getting the best signal amplifier. There's a lot of gimmicks out there that don't really do anything for your internet speed. Our favorite is the iBooster wi-fi repeater.  It's easy to use, reliable and effective.
